Hi, I'm an eastern 
woolly lemur! 
I live in trees but 
there aren't so many
on my island anymore.

I'm a grey
mouse lemur!

Hello! I'm a painted
mantella frog. I'm 
beautiful but toxic, 
be careful with me.

Hi! They call me
Tomato Frog 
because I inflate

Hey! I'm a 
Madagascar
Fire Millipede. 
Lemurs have a 
strange use for
me...

Watch out!
I'm a fossa and I 
eat lemurs! There
isn't much food 
anymore so I might
eat you!

Hi! I'm an aye aye
and my species is
endangered so I'm 
looking for bugs to eat!

Heeeeeeeeeeeey!

and I've got the moves
like Jackson!

Hello
They call me the
Satanic Leaf Tailed

Hi there!
I'm a black,
blue-eyed Lemuridae
but only the boys are 
actually black!

I'm a Panther
Chameleon, 
we're one of 
the most colourful
species of chameleon.

I'm a Lowland
Streaked Tenrec. 
I'm more closely
related to elephants
than to hedgehogs. 
Bugs are my favourite
food!

PIXELS   FOR   MADAGASCAR

in collaboration with Eden Projects

Lemursiv has been designed so that
all pixel art created on the island is
converted into donations which go 
directly to Eden Projects. All visitors 
can help save Madagascar from
deforestation by creating pixel art.

For next challenge

"/goto next"

in chat window

Madagascar used to be part of a 
supercontinent between Africa and India. 
Then, 88 million years ago, it separated 
becoming an island and developing an 
extraordinary ecosystem. Some of the many
endemic plants and animals can be seen on 
the island here.

CREATE   ART   PLANT   TREES
      PLANT   TREES   SAVE   LIVES

   bringing creativity and charity together
      in collaboration with Eden Projects

PIXELS   FOR   MADAGASCAR

in collaboration with Eden Projects

These are the main areas of focus for the 
reforestation of Madagascar lead by Eden
Projects and supported by Lemursiv.

Darwin's Orchid

Endemic to the island of
Madagascar, this plant 
caught the attention of 
Charles Darwin when he
visited. He predicted that 
there must be a moth on 
the island with a tongue at
least 20 cm long that could 
reach the nectar of the orchid's
stem. The moth was eventually
discovered and Darwin was proven
right posthumously.
Hello there! Welcome to my home, will you help save me and my friends?
My name is Liam, I'm trying to save my home Madagascar from deforestation. Will you help me by playing Lemursiv?

and this is my home,

This species of banana tree
is endemic to Madagascar 
but critically endangered. It's 
properties could be of great 
scientific use, allowing a disease
resistent species of banana tree
to be produced. Did you know 
bananas are in danger of 
extinction? Research the 
Panama disease to 
learn more.

The Baobab, also known
as the Monkey Bread Tree, 
is an emblematic feature in 
Madagascar. From nine 
species of baobabs found 
in the world, six of them 
only grow on Madagascar.

Welcome to mount
Maromokotro! People 
are cutting down trees
on my island and I don't
like it. Will you help me 
replant trees here?

I may look scary 
but I'm not very
adventurous... in 
the wild I only live
in one 10km2
forest. Please plant
trees there!

Hello! I'm a Madagascar
Long Eared Owl, would 
you like to take a tour
of the island on my back?

A Madagascar Long
Eared Owl nests here. 
Wait for him and he will 
give you a tour of his 
island.

I'm a Panther 
Chameleon, 
slurp!
